mxalloy third-party notices
===========================

mxalloy is Apache-2.0 licensed. Some model-family implementation code has additional
third-party provenance obligations:

diffusers / transformers
------------------------

The model-family implementations under `mxdiffusers/` — the FLUX.2 family (MMDiT
transformer, Qwen3 text encoder, AutoencoderKLFlux2 decoder, flow-match scheduler), the SDXL
family (UNet, CLIP text encoders, AutoencoderKL decoder, Euler scheduler), and the Z-Image
transformer — are independent MLX reimplementations derived from the Hugging Face
`diffusers` and `transformers` reference implementations.

Upstream: https://github.com/huggingface/diffusers, https://github.com/huggingface/transformers
Copyright (c) The HuggingFace Team. Licensed under the Apache License, Version 2.0
(http://www.apache.org/licenses/LICENSE-2.0). There is no diffusers runtime dependency.

Historical note: prior to 2026-06-11 the FLUX.2 family was an MLX port of mflux
(MIT, © Filip Strand, https://github.com/filipstrand/mflux) and releases from that period
carried its MIT notice. Those modules have been re-derived from the diffusers reference and
verified independently (see `mxdiffusers/PROVENANCE.md`); no mflux-derived code remains in
the current tree. mflux is still used in benchmarks as a runtime comparison baseline.
